					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-11959337#post-4674231</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-11959337/keeping-it-chill-with-your-homies-down-at-the-scp-foundation#post-4674231</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Tue, 02 Jun 2020 16:36:59 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>barredowl</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>6001754</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>See, I'm kinda frustrated on this one. Theoretically, I quite like the idea of the Foundation desperately trying to be relatable in a Broken Masquerade scenario <em>a la</em> every other modern company's Twitter account, but here I don't think this quite does it for me. There are some points where it kinda delves into an angle I really dig: namely, a glimpse into some of the Foundation's more shady business, such as with the D-Class implicitly commenting on how shit he has it at the Foundation. Unfortunately, to me a lot of the video seemed moreso a superficial commentary on researchers trying to relate to the youth rather than anything really interesting. There are smidgens of that idea sprinkled throughout the piece, and I found it a bit disappointing when that angle just wasn't properly explored.</p> <p>I understand that that's not really what this tale was going for, but the shallow interpretation which this story set up for me (namely, finding the main video/the side-reactions enjoyable) didn't entertain me enough, and got old real quickly. Personally, this didn't have any staying power, so unfortunately, this is a downvote from me.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
