					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-11959337#post-4263494</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-11959337/keeping-it-chill-with-your-homies-down-at-the-scp-foundation#post-4263494</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Mon, 27 May 2019 18:05:18 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Monteparnas</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>2926286</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>That's excellent, but maybe on the edge already.</p> <p>If it gets too cringe it becomes just not-fun, because it will then go beyond what is believable.</p> <p>For now I think it was on the spot: it shows an effort by researchers that are out-of-touch with the world to some degree, but just the degree you would expect. They have internet access, so keeping old style for children's shows, like sound effects from the 90's, makes sense, but missing the actual memes of their time do not. As it is, it is the balance that makes it a cringe fest, but a <em>believable</em> one.</p> <p>A thing I would change would be the appearance of 999. And not replacing it by Skippy, but actually I think they could conceivably show <strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">999 itself</span></strong> instead of a doctor. Let then also do something cool in the mix, they are still the Foundation, and they do have access to cool stuff, some of it quite safe to handle in a video.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
